description: From out- +‎ set, replacing earlier outsetting.

entries.meaning: Onset; the beginning or initial stage of something. [from 1759]
examples: He agreed and understood from the outset, so don't bother explaining again.

verbs.description: outset (third-person singular simple present outsets, present participle outsetting, simple past and past participle outset)

entries.meaning: (Internet, CSS, transitive) To cause (a design element) to extend around the outside of something else, the opposite of being inset.
